##### Basic grep Usage #####

ps aux | grep <searchTerm>			show all processes that contain the searchTerm
grep <searchTerm> <filename>			show all lines of a file that contain searchTerm
grep '^#' <filename>				search for comments in a file
grep -v '^#' <filename>				search for everything that isn't a comment in file
grep <searchTerm> <filename> -B 5		returns every match and 5 lines before it
grep <searchTerm> <filename> -A 5		returns every match and 5 lines after it
grep -e <searchTerm> -e <searcTerm> <filename>	search for multiple search terms

